A group of young Nigerians in the diaspora  have expressed optimism that the former governor of Anambra State and Labour Party(LP) Presidential candidate, Peter Obi would revamp the nation’s ailing economy if elected  as President in the 2023 General election The group, acting under the auspices of “Nigerian Youths Movement Diaspora Organisation” (NYMDO), South East Asia Chapter said “Obi appears to be the best candidate to bring about sustainable development needed to lift Nigeria out of her current pathetic and unfathomable condition” The release signed by the Group Coordinator Comrade . Kingsley Nwankwo, and made available to newsmen hinted that  “the candidature of the astute economist has no doubt brought a fresh air for the people of Nigeria since he opted to contest under the Labour Party. ” Obi’s economy policy and framework, if implemented in Nigeria, will make the country to rank among the best comity of states in Africa and in the world”.the statement reads in part While   also promising to  support the political aspiration of the LP Presidential Flagbearer , the group appealed to all Nigerians especially youths, who are more in numbers, to rally their support for “the vibrant, articulate and independent-minded politicians like Obi to emerge victorous at the forthcoming general elections. “The emergence of Mr. Obi as Nigerian President will not only assist the Country to regain her lost glory among the comity of States in the Worldover but will also correct many wrongs in the land and build hope and confidence of all and sundry in the Nigerian Project”. “The resolution on Obi is based on a far-reaching research support base, competency, vibrancy, economy policy, international repute/connections and team work antecedent of all the candidates vying for the number one seat in the country”. The group, however, described the former Anambra State Governor as “a forthright, reliable, sincere and vabriant politician who has contributed immensely to the development of Anambra State and the South East geo-political zone, as well as the entire entity of Nigeria. -Advertisement- POLL “Obi’s contributions in the areas of agriculture, healthcare delivery, road rehabilitation/construction, improved IGR, educational advancement, improved economy and adequate security of lives and properties, water supply and second to none investment drive during his eight years as a governor has made Anambra a virile state worthy of emulation to other states in the country. “Since the commencement for the agitation of sourcing for a competent, reliable and vabriant politician to pilot the affairs of the country in 2023 general elections after the expiration of the tenure of President Muhammadu Buhari, we came to realize more hidden qualities in Mr Peter Obi that are so remarkable such as humility, fairness, respect for elders and above all, his ability and readiness to serve with sincerity and fear of God. “Other areas are unparalleled and second to none manifesto and understanding of Nigerian terrain, problems and solutions which the former Anambra State governor has been making so explicity at every given opportunity”.